properties.areaDesc: San Diego County Mountains; San Diego County Deserts; Riverside County Mountains; Coachella Valley; San Bernardino County Mountains; San Gorgonio Pass Near Banning; Apple and Lucerne Valleys
properties.headline: Wind Advisory issued February 29 at 3:03AM PST until March 2 at 3:00AM PST by NWS San Diego CA
properties.description:
* WHAT...West winds 25 to 35 mph with gusts to 65 mph expected.
The strongest winds will surface on the mountains ridges and
down the eastern slopes into the lower deserts.

* WHERE...San Bernardino County Mountains, Riverside County
Mountains, San Diego County Mountains, Apple and Lucerne
Valleys, Coachella Valley, San Diego County Deserts and San
Gorgonio Pass Near Banning.

* WHEN...From 4 PM this afternoon to 3 AM PST Monday.

* IMPACTS...The strong winds will blow around unsecured objects.
Tree limbs could be blown down and a few power outages may
result. Visibilities will be reduced in blowing sand.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...High impact areas in the Coachella Valley
include Palm Springs, Palm Desert, La Quinta, I-10 and Highway
111. In the San Diego County deserts, Borrego Springs, Ocotillo
Wells, the Anza Borrego Desert and I-8 may all be impacted by
strong winds. In the High Desert, Highways 395, 18, 247 and I-15
may all be impacted by reduced visibilities in blowing sand.
properties.instruction:
Use extra caution when driving, especially if operating a high
profile vehicle. Secure outdoor objects.

NWSheadline: WIND ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 4 PM THIS AFTERNOON TO 3 AM PST MONDAY
